Capacitance of a capacitor ___________________________________________________________________
Capacitance of a capacitor = Charge / Potential Difference - Capacitance of a charged sphere = (4 * Pi * Permitivity of air) * Radius - Charge in a capacitor = Capacitance * Potential Difference
___________________________________________________________________
Electric Energy and Charge ___________________________________________________________________
Electric Charge = Current * Time - Electric Current = Voltage / Resistance - Electric Energy = Potential Difference * Current * Time - Electric Resistance = Voltage / Current - Electric Voltage = Current * Resistance ___________________________________________________________________
Electrostatics ___________________________________________________________________
Electrostatic field intensity = Force / Charge - Electrostatic field intensity between plates a distance apart = Voltage / Distance - E-Field intensity if charge is surrounded by material of permitivity = Charge / (4 * Pi * Force * Distance^2) - Energy stored in a charged capacitor = (0.5 * Capacitance) * Potential Difference^2 - Force on a current carrying conductor = Magnetic Flux Density * Current * Length of conductor - Force on an electron moving between charged plates = E-Field Intensity * Charge of electron - Force on moving charges = Magnetic Flux Density * Charge* Velocity of charge - Magnetic flux linkage through a coil = Number of turns * Field Strength * Area of coil - Permitivity of free space = (First charge * Second Charge ) / (4 * Pi * Force * Distance^2) - Potential difference between the two plates = Charge / Capacitance - E.M.F in a rod = Magnetic flux linkage * Distance moved by rod * Length of rod
___________________________________________________________________
Power ___________________________________________________________________
Power given Current and Resistance = (Current ^2) * Resistance - Power given Current and Voltage = Voltage * Current - Power given Voltage and Resistance = (Voltage ^2) * Resistance
___________________________________________________________________
Resistivity of a wire = Resistance of a wire / (Cross sectional area / length of wire) - Wavelength (De Broglie's Theory) = Plancks Constant / (Mass * Velocity) - Work done when moving a charge through a P.D = Charge * Potential Difference
